# No WordPress hosting dependency

The WordPress site at **www.jacobworsoe.dk** will be taken down. The Jekyll site **must not** reference it for:

- Images, downloads, or any files under `/wp-content/` or other WordPress paths
- Favicon or other static assets served only from WordPress
- “Canonical” links that assume the old WordPress URLs still work

**Do instead:**

- Host all images and static files under this repo (e.g. `assets/images/…` mirroring former `wp-content/uploads/…` paths)
- Use Jekyll `{{ '…' | relative_url }}` (or equivalent) in layouts/includes so paths work with `baseurl`
- Internal blog links should point to Jekyll URLs (same slugs as production), not hard-coded WordPress URLs
- Export scripts should rewrite WordPress media URLs to repo-relative Liquid when writing content

**MySQL export scripts** may still read WordPress **database** until cutover; that is separate from **runtime** references in the built site.
